---

<section class="section" id="calc">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The calculator</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Find your filing deadline.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Pick the tax year &mdash; the year the income was paid. The deadline shown is for filing in the following year.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="calc" data-calc data-select-formula="deadline">
      <form class="calc__form" aria-describedby="calc-disclaimer-top">
        <p class="calc__formnote" id="calc-disclaimer-top">Published IRS rules &mdash; confirm current-year dates on IRS.gov.</p>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="sel-year">Tax year <span class="intake-field__optional">year the income was paid</span></label>
          <select id="sel-year" data-calc-sel="year">
            <option value="2024">2024 (filed in 2025)</option>
            <option value="2025">2025 (filed in 2026)</option>
            <option value="2026">2026 (filed in 2027)</option>
            <option value="2027">2027 (filed in 2028)</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </form>

      <div class="calc__result" id="calc-result" role="status" aria-live="polite">
        <p class="calc__result-label">1099-NEC &amp; W-2 deadline</p>
        <p class="calc__result-range"><span data-out="primary">&mdash;</span></p>
        <ul class="calc__metrics">
          <li class="calc__metric"><span class="calc__metric-label">1099-MISC e-file to IRS</span><span class="calc__metric-value" data-out="m1">&mdash;</span></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="calc__result-why" data-out="text">Pick a tax year above to see the deadline.</p>
        <p class="calc__result-disclaimer">These are the published federal rules &mdash; <strong>always confirm the exact current-year dates on IRS.gov</strong>. State deadlines and penalties may differ, and this is general information, not tax advice.</p>
        <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg calc__result-cta" href="/contact/?intent=accounting" data-tb-event="calc_to_quote">Book the discovery call</a>
      </div>

      <noscript>
        <div class="calc__noscript">
          <p>The live calculator needs JavaScript. The core rule: <strong>1099-NEC and W-2 are due January 31</strong> of the year after the tax year (rolled to the next business day if that&rsquo;s a weekend); <strong>1099-MISC e-filed to the IRS is due March 31</strong>. Confirm exact dates on IRS.gov, or <a href="/contact/?intent=accounting">book a free discovery call</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </noscript>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="deadline-calc-how">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The rules behind it</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The 1099 &amp; W-2 deadlines that matter.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The federal filing calendar for the most common information returns &mdash; the same rules the calculator applies.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="vs-scroll">
      <table class="vs-table">
        <caption class="sr-only">Common information-return filing deadlines (federal).</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Form</th>
            <th scope="col">To recipient</th>
            <th scope="col" class="vs-table__us">To IRS / SSA</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>1099-NEC</strong> <span class="vs-table__concede">contractor pay</span></td><td>January 31</td><td class="vs-table__us"><strong>January 31</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>W-2</strong> <span class="vs-table__concede">employee wages</span></td><td>January 31</td><td class="vs-table__us"><strong>January 31</strong> (SSA)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>1099-MISC</strong> <span class="vs-table__concede">rents, other</span></td><td>January 31</td><td class="vs-table__us"><strong>Feb 28</strong> paper · <strong>Mar 31</strong> e-file</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="legal-doc__body stack-8">
      <p>Any deadline that lands on a Saturday, Sunday, or legal holiday rolls to the next business day &mdash; the calculator applies that roll to the January 31 dates automatically. Send recipient copies and file with the IRS/SSA by the dates shown; e-filing is required once you hit the IRS volume threshold for information returns.</p>
      <p>Late or incorrect filings carry penalties <em>per form</em>, and they scale with how late you are &mdash; which is why clean, current books and accurate contractor records through the year matter more than a last-minute scramble. This page is general information, not tax advice; your CPA files the returns, and we keep the underlying records right.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="deadline-calc-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">1099 deadlines, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="deadline-calc-next">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where to go next.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for card in nextCards %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>{{ card.name }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ card.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="{{ card.href }}">{{ card.cta }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="deadline-calc-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Questions about 1099 deadlines.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="deadline-calc-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="deadline-calc-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
